## Publish to GitHub Pages

Two options:

### A. Automated (recommended) — GitHub Actions

This repo includes `.github/workflows/publish.yml`, which renders the site and
deploys it on every push to `main`.

1. Push the repository to GitHub.
2. In **Settings → Pages**, set **Source** to **GitHub Actions**.
3. Push to `main`. The action builds `_site/` and deploys it. Your site will be
   at `https://<user>.github.io/<repo>/`.
4. Update the `github` link in `_quarto.yml` (`website.navbar.tools`) to point
   at your repository.

### B. Manual — `quarto publish`

```bash
quarto publish gh-pages
```

This renders and pushes to a `gh-pages` branch. Then set **Settings → Pages →
Source** to **Deploy from a branch** and choose `gh-pages`.

> **Project vs. user site paths:** the quiz loads the CSV via a relative path,
> so it works whether the site is served from a subpath
> (`user.github.io/repo/`) or a root domain. No base-URL configuration needed.

